name: Birdman and the Galaxy Trio
overview:
Birdman and the Galaxy Trio is an animated science fiction television series created by Alex Toth and produced by Hanna-Barbera. It debuted on NBC on September 9, 1967, and ran on Saturday mornings until September 6, 1969. The program consists of two segments: Birdman, depicting the adventures of a winged superhero powered by the sun, and The Galaxy Trio, centering around the exploits of three extraterrestrial superheroes. NBC ran two new segments of Birdman each Saturday, separated by a segment of The Galaxy Trio.

The character of Birdman was revived three decades later in the Cartoon Network/Adult Swim TV series Harvey Birdman, Attorney at Law, and several characters from Birdman and the Galaxy Trio appeared in this revival.

episodes.name: X The Eliminator
episodes.overview: X the Eliminator is hired by the criminal agency F.E.A.R. to destroy Birdman, and to retrieve the crest from his helmet as proof.

episodes.name: Revolt of the Robots
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio receives an S.O.S. from the planet Orbus-4, where the robot servants have revolted.

episodes.name: Morto The Marauder
episodes.overview: The evil genius Morto escapes from prison in a bullet-proof suit of armor.

episodes.name: The Ruthless Ringmaster
episodes.overview: A circus troupe goes on a crime spree, stealing top-secret weapons.

episodes.name: The Battle of the Aquatrons
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio investigate a beam from the formerly peaceful planet Aqueous, which is melting the Earth's icecaps.

episodes.name: Birdman Versus The Mummer
episodes.overview: The Mummer, master of disguise, imitates a slew of people, including the King of Salaban, to force a war with Lanpeer.

episodes.name: The Quake Threat
episodes.overview: Evil genius Professor Kyroff has developed a device that causes earthquakes, and plans to sell his invention to the highest bidder.

episodes.name: The Galaxy Trio Versus The Moltens of Meteorus
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio receives an urgent S.O.S. from Meteor Man's home planet Meteorus, where the deadly Moltens are causing volcanic eruptions, planning to cover the planet in a blanket of lava.

episodes.name: Avenger For Ransom
episodes.overview: Zardo has kidnapped Birdman's eagle companion Avenger, and holds him ransom, forcing Birdman to steal military plans for Avenger's return.

episodes.name: Birdman Versus Cumulus, the Storm King
episodes.overview: Cumulus, using his control over the elements, holds Central City ransom.

episodes.name: The Galaxy Trio and the Sleeping Planet
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio are sent to check out planet K-7, when that planet misses international roll call.

episodes.name: Serpents of The Deep
episodes.overview: When sharks steal an important government bathyscaphe, Birdman goes to the bottom of the ocean to investigate.

episodes.name: Nitron The Human Bomb
episodes.overview: Nitron, a former scientist changed by an accident involving nitro-hydrogen, tries to join F.E.A.R. (and take charge) by completing three impossible criminal tasks.

episodes.name: The Galaxy Trio and the Peril of the Prison Planet
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio are heading for a vacation, when they receive an S.O.S. from a prison planet.

episodes.name: Mentor, The Mind Taker
episodes.overview: Mentor uses his powers of the mind to force Avenger to attack Birdman.

episodes.name: The Purple Moss
episodes.overview: Birdman investigates a strange indestructible purple moss that begins spreading over the nation's farmland.

episodes.name: Drackmore, The Despot
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio investigate the disappearance of pioneer spaceships in the Tranquility Belt.

episodes.name: The Deadly Trio
episodes.overview: Dr. Zardo, Dr. Quint, and Dr. Killee decide to join forces to destroy Birdman.

episodes.name: The Brain Thief
episodes.overview: Dr Shado, the brain thief, is kidnapping the country's top scientists, and stealing their mental prowess.

episodes.name: Titan, the Titanium Man
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio respond to a phony distress call from the planet Titanorus, where a scrawny scientist has succeeded in transforming himself into Titan, the Titanium Man.

episodes.name: Birdman Versus The Constrictor
episodes.overview: The Constrictor steals the missile defense location plans for all the free nations, and offers to exchange the plans, for Avenger, Birdman's eagle companion.

episodes.name: Number One
episodes.overview: Number One, Birdman's arch-enemy, lures Birdman into a trap to steal his solar powers.

episodes.name: The Duplitrons
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio are summoned to Earth, where the  leaders of the three largest countries are planning to declare war on each other.

episodes.name: Birdman Meets Birdgirl
episodes.overview: As Birdman is about to receive a medal from Central City, Birdgirl reveals herself, when she saves everyone at the ceremony.  She destroys Birdman's reputation among the city leaders, claiming Birdman has taken credit for her achievements.

episodes.name: Birdman Meets Reducto
episodes.overview: Reducto uses his Reductron Machine on Birdman and reduces him to the size of an insect!

episodes.name: Computron Lives
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio is summoned for help, after criminals reactivate the rebellious robot Computron,

episodes.name: Vulturo, Prince of Darkness
episodes.overview: Agents of the dread organization F.E.A.R. offer Vulturo one million dollars if he can eliminate Birdman.

episodes.name: The Chameleon
episodes.overview: The Chameleon, an evil scientist who has perfected a shape-shifting formula, uses his powers to steal precious art and diamonds.

episodes.name: The Eye of Time
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio encounter strange space turbulence which sends them back in time, where they encounter Vikings who mistake them for invading Romans.

episodes.name: The Incredible Magnatroid
episodes.overview: The mad scientist Metallo creates a magnetized robot to do his evil bidding.

episodes.name: Hannibal The Hunter
episodes.overview: Hannibal prides himself on being a great hunter, and lures Birdman to his island in order to add him to his trophy collection.

episodes.name: The Galaxy Trio and the Cavemen of Primevia
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio encounters an out-of-control spaceship.  We they capture it, they find a man fleeing from the mines where he is forced to work as a slave.

episodes.name: The Empress of Evil
episodes.overview: The evil sorceress Medusa captures Prince Jhao, son of Birdman's friend the Maharaja of Ramapur.

episodes.name: The Wings of F.E.A.R.
episodes.overview: Agents of F.E.A.R. have kidnapped three ambassadors from the Conference of Peaceful Nations Building, in a bid to frighten world leaders away from cooperation there.

episodes.name: The Demon Raiders
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio must intervene when the Intergalactic Treasury Building on Centauri-3 is attacked by Zykor.

episodes.name: Birdman Meets Birdboy
episodes.overview: Birdman discovers a boy floating in a life raft.  Upon determining that the boy is near death, Birdman infuses the boy with with his own solar powers.

episodes.name: The Menace Of Dr. Millenium
episodes.overview: Dr Millenium perfects his Millenium Machine, which allows him to bring prehistoric creatures back to life, and use them for his nefarious ends.

episodes.name: The Rock Men
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio must rescue Plutonian geologist Ekon, when rock formations come to life and take him captive.

episodes.name: Birdman Versus Dr. Freezoids
episodes.overview: The newest member of F.E.A.R., Dr. Freezoids, uses his freeze ray in the service of that treacherous organization.

episodes.name: The Deadly Duplicator
episodes.overview: A mysterious villain with the power to create an exact replica of a person replaces key military personnel with their duplicates.

episodes.name: Space Fugitives
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio is framed for attacking planets and robbing them of scientific equipment!

episodes.name: Professor Nightshade
episodes.overview: Professor Nightshade, an agent of F.E.A.R., steals a dangerous new invention.

episodes.name: Train Trek
episodes.overview: Spyero plots to steal a Space Capsule by swapping the Atomic City supply train with his own.

episodes.name: Space Slaves
episodes.overview: Elrath uses a long-distance displacer ray to kidnap Gravity Girl to the Pyramid Planet in the mysterious Crimson Zone.

episodes.name: Birdman Meets Moray of the Deep
episodes.overview: The devious Captain Moray uses false distress calls to trap ship and kidnap the scientists they carry.

episodes.name: Birdman and The Monster of the Mountains
episodes.overview: Birdman and Birdboy check out a report of a monster terrorizing villages high in the Himalayas.

episodes.name: The Galaxy Trio Versus Growliath
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio is summoned to investigate when tiny creatures are made large by the evil scientist Growliath.

episodes.name: The Return of Vulturo
episodes.overview: Vuluro returns with a robot Avenger for revenge on Birdman.

episodes.name: The Revenge of Dr. Millenium
episodes.overview: Birdman vanishes, and reappears in Ancient China, thanks to the dastardly devices invented by Dr. Millenium, out for revenge.

episodes.name: Return to Aqueous
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio receive a call for assistance from the  peaceful citizens of Aqueous, who are under attack from a monster who can breathe lightning and project powerful heat rays from his arms.

episodes.name: The Ant Ape
episodes.overview: Professor Klaw has created "Ant Ape", a nearly invincible creature, with whom he plans to get his revenge on Birdman.

episodes.name: Birdman Versus The Speed Demon
episodes.overview: A prisoner mixing chemicals in prison has a fortuitous accident when an explosion gives him the power of super-speed.

episodes.name: Invasion of the Sporoids
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio investigates as a number of outposts have gone silent, and discover a monster that divides into more monsters when they attack!

episodes.name: The Wild Weird West
episodes.overview: Jesse Johns, descendant of the infamous Jesse James, is getting help from a mad scientist. Doctor Cordo has given the outlaw special gear: robotic horses, lasers, and paralyzer beams.  They're making fools of law and order!

episodes.name: The Pirate Plot
episodes.overview: Captain Kidd, infamous pirate, has been resurrected and armed with modern super-weapons by Doctor Demon.

episodes.name: Gralik of Gravitas
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio rush to help King Gramor, Gravity Girl's father.

episodes.name: Skon of Space
episodes.overview: Falcon 7 warns Birdman that a strange unidentified spacecraft has been seen near the Bird Lair.

episodes.name: Murro the Marauder
episodes.overview: Murro the Marauder possesses the power to bring other people's shadows to life, and uses that power to take over F.E.A.R.

episodes.name: Plastus the Pirate Planet
episodes.overview: The Galaxy Trio answers a distress call from planet Z-11, as an artificial planetoid hurtles toward them.

episodes.name: Morto Rides Again
episodes.overview: Morto the Marauder escapes from prison again, this time by converting a boiler from the prison laundry into a rocket.
